description: The National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA) is a national intelligence and combat support agency of the U.S. Department of Defense (DOD). I was recruited to work there upon graduating from UNC-G. The places I went and work I performed in service to the United States taught me personal and professional lessons that I will carry with me through my career. My customers - those using the information I provided - included intelligence operatives and fellow analysts, special operators, DOD leadership, and the President of the United States. Whether stationed Washington, D.C., Iraq, Afghanistan, or Ft. Bragg, NC, this was the constant: I was a part of and led teams that constructed products (our analysis of issues, questions, and events) for numerous customers, all of whom wanted to be treated as if they were our ONLY customer. These products had to be correct and on time, every time. Human lives and U.S. national security interests depended on it. Life goals, namely my wife's and my desire to settle down in close proximity to family, led me away from government work and into business. Just as lives were on the line while I served my country, livelihoods are at issue as I serve my customers today.
